    <s1 name="Available Documentations">
      <p>If available, the documents related to the used release will be
      identified by the same tag. Example, "Installing the 3.6 release" is
      what should be read for installing JORAM 3.6.</p>
      <p>It may happen that for a given release, no document match. This means
      that the document written for the previous release is still up-to-date.
      Example, "Installing the 3.4 release" is what should be read for
      installing JORAM 3.5.</p>
      <p>It is well known by the JORAM team that this documentation is not
      sufficient and sometimes vague or unclear. Do not hesitate to provide
      any comment or feedback that could help us improving the doc. Also, 
      any contribution is welcome.</p>
    </s1>

